# 🎮 Play & Conquer

A collection of interactive browser-based mini games and programming exercises developed using **HTML**, **CSS**, and **JavaScript**. This project was created as a college assignment to practice front-end web development and JavaScript programming concepts.

> **Note:** This project was developed with AI assistance as part of the learning process. The focus was on understanding, integrating, testing, and customizing the application while learning web development.

---

## 📌 Features

- 🏠 Home page
- ❓ Quiz Challenge
- 🃏 Flip Card Game
- 🧩 Drag & Drop Activity
- 💻 Code Match Challenge
- 🤔 Guess the Output
- ⚡ Rapid Fire Quiz
- ✅ True or False Challenge
- 🐞 Debug Challenge
- 📱 Responsive design

---

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

- HTML5
- CSS3
- JavaScript (Vanilla)

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```
play-and-conquer/
│
├── css/
├── images/
├── js/
├── index.html
├── quiz.html
├── flipcard.html
├── dragdrop.html
├── codematch.html
├── guessoutput.html
├── rapidfire.html
├── truefalse.html
├── debug.html
└── README.md
```

---

## 🚀 Getting Started

1. Download or clone the repository.

```bash
git clone https://github.com/axwin-raj/play-and-conquer.git
```

2. Open the project folder.

3. Double-click **index.html**
   or open it with any modern web browser.

No installation or additional software is required.

---

## 🎯 Learning Objectives

- Practice HTML page structure
- Improve CSS styling skills
- Learn JavaScript DOM manipulation
- Build interactive browser games
- Understand event handling and user interaction

